      "Stoicism has profoundly influenced Western thought, shaping ethical and political philosophies for centuries.",
      "Its principles are integrated into modern cognitive-behavioral therapy (CBT), helping individuals manage anxiety, depression, and other mental health challenges by reframing negative thought patterns. For example, the Stoic practice of premeditatio malorum (premeditation of evils) is used in CBT to help individuals prepare for potential setbacks and develop coping strategies."
